WEBVTT

00:04.938 --> 00:05.905 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Good evening.

00:05.939 --> 00:06.906 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm Judy Woodruff.

00:06.940 --> 00:08.742 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
On the "NewsHour" tonight:

00:08.775 --> 00:10.977 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP, President of the
United States:
Twenty-three of the 28 member
nations are

00:11.011 --> 00:13.046 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
still not paying what they
should be paying.

00:13.079 --> 00:19.252 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: President Trump
abroad, today
in Brussels, reprimands fellow
NATO leaders

00:19.285 --> 00:24.257 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
over unpaid dues, but is silent
on NATO's
joint defense pact.

00:24.290 --> 00:27.093 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Then: the Manchester attack.

00:27.127 --> 00:33.433 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Britain remains on high alert,
as U.S. intelligence-sharing
in the investigation was
temporarily halted,

00:33.466 --> 00:36.636 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
a casualty of media leaks.

00:36.669 --> 00:38.371 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And gender on the job.

00:38.405 --> 00:42.308 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Is testosterone an indicator of
who takes
risk at work?

00:42.342 --> 00:45.545 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
JENNIFER LERNER, Harvard
University: There's
a systematic relationship there.

00:45.578 --> 00:50.917 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And it's all explained through
testosterone
as a kind of social dominance
hormone.

00:50.950 --> 00:57.690 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: All that and more
on tonight's
"PBS NewsHour."

00:57.724 --> 00:59.759 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

00:59.793 --> 01:12.138 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: A note of some
discord today,
as President Trump addressed his
first meeting

01:12.172 --> 01:13.907 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of NATO leaders.

01:13.940 --> 01:19.112 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He criticized the allies, again,
for falling
short on their share of defense
spending.

01:19.145 --> 01:23.383 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
From Brussels, special
correspondent Ryan
Chilcote begins our coverage.

01:23.416 --> 01:28.521 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RYAN CHILCOTE: Jets blazed over
Brussels and
NATO's gleaming new headquarters
this afternoon,

01:28.555 --> 01:33.460 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the flags of all 28 member
states making a
show of unity.

01:33.493 --> 01:37.664 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But a short time earlier, with
his fellow
leaders looking on, President
Trump renewed

01:37.697 --> 01:41.267 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
his longstanding demand: NATO
allies must
do more.

01:41.301 --> 01:44.637 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP, President of the
United States:
Member nations are still not
paying what they

01:44.671 --> 01:51.945 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
should be paying and what they
are supposed
to be paying for their defense.

01:51.978 --> 01:56.983 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This is not fair to the people
and taxpayers
of the United States.

01:57.016 --> 02:01.387 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And many of these nations owe
massive amounts
of money from past years.

02:01.421 --> 02:05.291 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RYAN CHILCOTE: The president
noted the bloc
did, however, shell out for a
new home.

02:05.325 --> 02:13.099 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP: I never asked once
what the
new NATO headquarters cost.

02:13.133 --> 02:15.502 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I refuse to do that.

02:15.535 --> 02:17.437 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
But it is beautiful.

02:17.470 --> 02:21.141 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RYAN CHILCOTE: German Chancellor
Angela Merkel,
speaking before the president,
struck a different

02:21.174 --> 02:23.776 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
note in unveiling a memorial to
the Berlin
Wall.

02:23.810 --> 02:26.779 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ANGELA MERKEL, German Chancellor
(through
translator): Our alliance is
united in the

02:26.813 --> 02:30.116 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
awareness of the importance of
cooperation
to insist on freedom.

02:30.150 --> 02:34.954 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It is not isolation and the
building of walls
that make us successful, but
open societies

02:34.988 --> 02:36.823 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
that share the same values.

02:36.856 --> 02:40.894 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
RYAN CHILCOTE: NATO's
secretary-general said
the unveilings of the wall and
wreckage from

02:40.927 --> 02:45.031 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the World Trade Center in New
York signify
the importance of the alliance.

02:45.064 --> 02:48.401 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JENS STOLTENBERG, NATO
Secretary-General:
We saw the strength of that bond
after the

02:48.434 --> 02:57.443 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
9/11 attacks, and for the first
time, NATO
invoked our collective defense
clause, Article

02:57.477 --> 03:01.848 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
V, one for all and all for one.

03:01.881 --> 03:07.187 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RYAN CHILCOTE: Mr. Trump didn't
explicitly
endorse Article V, the first
president who

03:07.220 --> 03:11.524 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
hasn't since the alliance's
founding in 1949.

03:11.558 --> 03:17.197 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
After calling NATO obsolete last
year, a comment
he's since walked back, NATO
leaders seemed

03:17.230 --> 03:18.898 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
dismayed.

03:18.932 --> 03:22.602 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
President Trump did, though,
appear to push
the prime minister of Montenegro
aside as

03:22.635 --> 03:28.474 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
leaders moved through a hall,
all of this
in a city that candidate Trump
called a hellhole

03:28.508 --> 03:30.410 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
last year.

03:30.443 --> 03:36.082 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
President Trump has also
criticized the European
Union, the other big institution
headquartered

03:36.115 --> 03:40.787 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
in Brussels, applauding
Britain's decision
to exit the bloc.

03:40.820 --> 03:45.425 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The E.U.'s two leaders who share
the job of
running the bloc of 28
countries, the president

03:45.458 --> 03:49.696 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of the European commission,
Jean-Claude Juncker,
and the president of the
European Council,

03:49.729 --> 03:52.966 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Donald Tusk, also met President
Trump today.

03:52.999 --> 03:55.501 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
After the meeting, it was clear
that differences
remained.

03:55.535 --> 04:01.274 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DONALD TUSK, European Council
President: Some
issues remain open, like climate
and trade.

04:01.307 --> 04:07.647 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I am not 100 percent sure
that we can
say today -- we means Mr.
President and myself

04:07.680 --> 04:13.286 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
-- that we have a common
position, common
opinion about Russia.

04:13.319 --> 04:17.690 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RYAN CHILCOTE: The new American
president
also held his first meeting with
France's

04:17.724 --> 04:20.927 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
newly elected president,
Emmanuel Macron.

04:20.960 --> 04:26.799 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
The handshake lasted six
seconds, and the
39-year-old Frenchman held his
own.

04:26.833 --> 04:32.138 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In private, the president of
France urged
Mr. Trump to respect the Paris
climate agreement.

04:32.171 --> 04:38.544 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Finally, after a long day in
Brussels, the
president flew on to Sicily for
the G7 summit

04:38.578 --> 04:40.179 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
tomorrow.

04:40.213 --> 04:44.317 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And a short time
ago, I spoke
with Ryan Chilcote from
Brussels.

04:44.350 --> 04:46.219 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Ryan, welcome.

04:46.252 --> 04:51.090 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, how did the European leaders
react to
President Trump's criticisms
today?

04:51.124 --> 04:56.996 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RYAN CHILCOTE: Well, they have
been very reserved,
very guarded in their response
to President

04:57.030 --> 04:58.865 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Trump's criticism today.

04:58.898 --> 05:03.102 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Don't forget that a good number
of the leaders,
in fact, those that President
Trump, I think,

05:03.136 --> 05:08.174 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
has been hardest on when it
comes to their
commitments to NATO, are going
to see him

05:08.207 --> 05:12.078 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in Sicily tomorrow, so they
don't want a spat
with President Trump.

05:12.111 --> 05:17.517 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But, you know, they will clearly
be very disappointed
by the criticism today.

05:17.550 --> 05:23.890 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
A lot of them feel that the
place where President
Trump delivered his criticism
was the wrong

05:23.923 --> 05:29.762 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
place to do it, beside this
memorial that
effectively wasn't just to U.S.
troops, but

05:29.796 --> 05:37.570 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
also to NATO troops who have
lost their lives
in Afghanistan fighting
alongside the United

05:37.603 --> 05:41.074 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
States after NATO invoked
Article V.

05:41.107 --> 05:44.310 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So they don't like where the
comments were
made.

05:44.344 --> 05:48.614 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And then the other issue, of
course, is that
many of them disagree that
they're not doing

05:48.648 --> 05:54.921 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
enough or moving in the right
direction to
support NATO in terms of their
military spending.

05:54.954 --> 06:00.326 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The president pointed out that
23 out of the
28 NATO members are not spending
2 percent

06:00.360 --> 06:05.098 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of their budgets on the military
at this point
-- of their GDP.

06:05.131 --> 06:11.604 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And they will say that, in fact,
if you look
at the commitment, they have
until 2024 to

06:11.637 --> 06:13.406 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
do that.

06:13.439 --> 06:16.209 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And here at NATO, from the NATO
officials
I have talked to, they believe
that the vast

06:16.242 --> 06:21.514 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
majority of the NATO countries
are well on
their way with verifiable plans
to do that,

06:21.547 --> 06:24.384 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
with the notable exception of
Germany.

06:24.417 --> 06:29.956 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But they weren't showing that
because they
want to work with President
Trump, and they

06:29.989 --> 06:34.394 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
clearly believe -- and that was
very apparent
in the language, the body
language today -- that

06:34.427 --> 06:37.063 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
this is a president that they
need to win
over.

06:37.096 --> 06:42.935 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They need to assure him that
NATO is something
that's in the United States'
interest.

06:42.969 --> 06:46.105 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Very quickly,
Ryan, you were
just in Russia.

06:46.139 --> 06:49.075 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
You covered the Kremlin for,
what, 20 years.

06:49.108 --> 06:52.779 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What do you think Russia, the
Russian officials
are thinking about today's
meeting?

06:52.812 --> 06:56.249 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RYAN CHILCOTE: Well, I wouldn't
say that they
would be delighted with today's
meeting, because,

06:56.282 --> 06:59.218 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
of course, they're never
delighted by anything
that NATO does.

06:59.252 --> 07:02.622 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They see NATO as a threat to
Russia.

07:02.655 --> 07:05.958 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But they will be happier about
this meeting
than they were about the meeting
that we saw

07:05.992 --> 07:07.827 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
last year or the year before.

07:07.860 --> 07:14.400 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Remember, it was at those
meetings that NATO
took a very hard line on Russia
in the aftermath

07:14.434 --> 07:16.602 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of Russia's intervention in
Ukraine.

07:16.636 --> 07:22.341 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It was those meetings that led
to the deployment
of about 3,000 NATO troops,
troops under NATO's

07:22.375 --> 07:27.480 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
command right really at Russia's
border in
the Baltic countries and in
Poland.

07:27.513 --> 07:34.387 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And the fact that we didn't get
that explicit
expression of support from
Article V from

07:34.420 --> 07:38.624 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
President Trump today, these are
the things
that the Russians will be very
pleased about.

07:38.658 --> 07:44.430 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And, finally, any
sense of
what the Trump administration,
the Trump delegation

07:44.464 --> 07:45.731 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
thinks about all this?

07:45.765 --> 07:48.201 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
RYAN CHILCOTE: Well, they said
that the meeting
was a success.

07:48.234 --> 07:50.837 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Sean Spicer spoke with reporters
after.

07:50.870 --> 07:55.942 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And he said that, you know, the
president's
hard line, if you will, the
criticism that

07:55.975 --> 08:01.080 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
he has been consistent with for
the last year-and-a-half,
is really paying dividends.

08:01.113 --> 08:06.452 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He said that the meeting, the
dinner meeting,
tonight started with a
discussion about how

08:06.486 --> 08:11.457 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the countries can share more of
the burden,
how they can participate in
counterterrorism

08:11.491 --> 08:12.925 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
along with the United States.

08:12.959 --> 08:16.095 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Those have been two key demands
from President
Trump.

08:16.128 --> 08:22.635 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And really, Sean Spicer, for
one, played down
the idea that President Trump
should have

08:22.668 --> 08:31.010 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
explicitly supported or endorsed
Article V,
you know, saying, look, he was
there to dedicate

08:31.043 --> 08:37.283 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
-- to read the dedication, to
give a speech
at a memorial that is called
Article V and

08:37.316 --> 08:39.085 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
9/11.

08:39.118 --> 08:42.989 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, of course, the president
even by just
being here at the NATO meeting
supports Article

08:43.022 --> 08:43.956 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
V.

08:43.990 --> 08:45.725 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, he has pushed back on all
that.

08:45.758 --> 08:50.096 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They see the president's tough
line here at
NATO and in Europe in general as
the right

08:50.129 --> 08:53.432 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
approach, the only way that's
going to get
the goods that they want
delivered.

08:53.466 --> 08:59.705 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Ryan Chilcote,
covering today's
NATO meeting in Brussels, thank
you.

08:59.739 --> 09:04.176 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In the day's other news: A
federal appeals
court in Richmond, Virginia,
upheld a lower

09:04.210 --> 09:08.581 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
court ruling that blocked
President Trump's
revised travel ban.

09:08.614 --> 09:13.486 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The appellate judges of the
Fourth Circuit
said the policy, targeting six
mostly Muslim

09:13.519 --> 09:17.023 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
nations -- quote -- "drips with
religious
intolerance."

09:17.056 --> 09:20.593 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's the first appeals court to
rule on the
revised ban.

09:20.626 --> 09:25.231 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Justice Department says that
it will appeal
to the U.S. Supreme Court.

09:25.264 --> 09:30.836 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Pentagon has concluded that
a U.S. airstrike
in Iraq last March led to the
death of at

09:30.870 --> 09:33.439 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
least 105 civilians.

09:33.472 --> 09:38.578 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It happened in Mosul, where
government forces
are fighting to retake the city
from the Islamic

09:38.611 --> 09:40.413 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
State group.

09:40.446 --> 09:45.318 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Investigators say they found
that a U.S. bomb
dropped on a building set off
explosives that

09:45.351 --> 09:47.353 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ISIS fighters had planted
inside.

09:47.386 --> 09:52.158 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The airstrike was originally
intended to kill
two snipers.

09:52.191 --> 09:57.830 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
China's government is protesting
after a U.S.
warship sailed close to manmade
islands in

09:57.863 --> 09:59.765 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
the South China Sea today.

09:59.799 --> 10:05.905 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The guided missile destroyer
Dewey came within
12 nautical miles of Mischief
Reef, which

10:05.938 --> 10:08.040 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the Chinese now claim.

10:08.074 --> 10:13.245 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In Beijing, a Foreign Ministry
spokesman said
the U.S. challenge hurts efforts
to resolve

10:13.279 --> 10:15.047 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
disputes.

10:15.081 --> 10:17.683 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
LU KANG, Chinese Foreign
Ministry Spokesman
(through translator): The U.S.'
actions bring

10:17.717 --> 10:23.155 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
severe disruptions to the
process of negotiations,
and can only bring harm and not
benefits.

10:23.189 --> 10:28.461 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
China's resolve to protect its
sovereign territory,
security and maritime interests
is resolute.

10:28.494 --> 10:32.798 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The U.S. disputes
China's claim
and says that it will continue
to conduct

10:32.832 --> 10:36.168 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
freedom of navigation exercises
in the area.

10:36.202 --> 10:39.505 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This was the first one since
President Trump
took office.

10:39.538 --> 10:44.210 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Government troops in the
Philippines launched
a new operation today to retake
control of

10:44.243 --> 10:47.446 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
a southern city from Islamist
militants.

10:47.480 --> 10:51.450 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Soldiers arrived in Marawi
backed by tanks
and attack helicopters.

10:51.484 --> 10:57.390 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The rebels have sealed off much
